TITLE: Why major commercial real estate firms are joining resources to recruit Black student-athletes
SUMMARY: A paid internship program that teaches the fundamentals of real estate investing has launched a new partnership with Black student-athletes.

TITLE: Ford's EV charging deal with Tesla puts pressure on GM, other rival automakers
SUMMARY: A surprise deal between Ford and Tesla on electric vehicle charging technology and infrastructure could put new pressure on other automakers' EV strategies.

TITLE: JPMorgan Chase cut about 500 jobs this week, including technology and operations roles
SUMMARY: Like many financial firms, JPMorgan periodically trims staff during the year, even as it hires thousands more workers to fill roles.

TITLE: Disney rips DeSantis bid to disqualify judge in free speech lawsuit
SUMMARY: Disney urged a federal court to reject a request by Florida Gov. Ron DeSantis to disqualify the judge overseeing the company's lawsuit against the governor.

TITLE: Disney still has plans to spend billions in Florida despite its battle with DeSantis
SUMMARY: Disney's fight with the Florida governor has taken on new significance now that DeSantis is running for president.

TITLE: Ford EVs will use Tesla charging tech in surprise partnership between rival automakers
SUMMARY: Ford Motor will partner with Tesla on several charging initiatives for its current and future electric vehicles in an unusual tie-up.

TITLE: JPMorgan is developing a ChatGPT-like A.I. service that gives investment advice
SUMMARY: Banks including Goldman Sachs and Morgan Stanley are testing A.I. internally, but JPMorgan may be the first to release a GPT-like product directly to customers.

TITLE: DirecTV reaches deal to provide NFL 'Sunday Ticket' to bars and restaurants
SUMMARY: DirecTV gave up NFL Sunday Ticket residential rights for next season, but it will continue to be the commercial provider for the package.

TITLE: Gap shares soar after retailer reports big improvement in margins
SUMMARY: Apparel retailer Gap reported another quarter of net losses and sale dips across its four brands but did manage to significantly improve its margins.

TITLE: Ford CEO Jim Farley says Chinese automakers such as BYD are its greatest EV rivals
SUMMARY: Ford CEO Jim Farley used Warren Buffett-backed BYD as the prime example of a Chinese automaker that has successfully developed and sold electric vehicles.

TITLE: Illumina shareholders oust board chair, CEO survives Carl Icahn proxy battle
SUMMARY: Carl Icahn has accused Illumina's management and board of poor oversight, particularly with regard to the company's acquisition of cancer test maker Grail.

TITLE: JPMorgan Chase says Jeffrey Epstein paid tuition for kids of U.S. Virgin Islands governor
SUMMARY: The U.S. Virgin Islands alleges in a lawsuit JPMorgan Chase facilitated sex trafficking by Jeffrey Epstein, a predator who lived in the American territory.

TITLE: Dollar Tree shares plunge after company misses on earnings, slashes full-year profit outlook
SUMMARY: Dollar Tree disappointed Wall Street Thursday after it reduced its profit outlook for the year and missed on earnings estimates, sending shares plunging.

TITLE: Best Buy shares rise on earnings beat, even as CEO says shoppers are showing 'recessionary behaviors'
SUMMARY: Best Buy shares rose, but the retailer expects weaker spending on consumer electronics the rest of the year.

TITLE: NRO director says commercial space industry helps fuel the spy satellite agency’s ambitious goals
SUMMARY: NRO Director Chris Scolese said the agency is looking to advance new technologies like artificial intelligence, machine learning and quantum sensing.

TITLE: FDA grants full approval to Pfizer Covid treatment Paxlovid for high-risk adults
SUMMARY: Pfizer and the FDA view Paxlovid as an important complementary tool to vaccination that can help high-risk Americans manage their Covid infections.

TITLE: Virgin Galactic completes Unity 25 spaceflight in key final test before commercial service
SUMMARY: It's a crucial moment for Virgin Galactic, which has suffered repeated setbacks, several disasters and years of delays in developing its spaceflight system.

TITLE: Sandra Douglass Morgan helped shape sports betting around the country. Now she's leading the NFL's Raiders
SUMMARY: Sandra Douglass Morgan became a gaming regulator the same year the Supreme Court cleared the path for legalized sports betting.

TITLE: Kohl's shares jump as retailer reports a surprise profit
SUMMARY: Kohl's unexpectedly posted a profit and reaffirmed its full-year guidance.

TITLE: Not just Disney: DeSantis brings history of business battles to the presidential campaign
SUMMARY: Ron DeSantis is slated to launch his presidential campaign on Twitter during a conversation with Elon Musk, becoming Donald Trump's top rival.

TITLE: American Eagle Outfitters shares sink as retailer lowers forecast
SUMMARY: The mall-based retailer's results diverged from Abercrombie & Fitch's earlier in the day.

TITLE: Citigroup to spin off its Mexico business, Banamex, after sale efforts collapse
SUMMARY: Citigroup announced Wednesday it plans to pursue an initial public offering of its Mexico business, ditching long-running sales talks with several suitors.

TITLE: Iconic singer Tina Turner dies at 83
SUMMARY: Singer Tina Turner has died at the age of 83 after a long illness, a spokesperson said Wednesday.

TITLE: Abercrombie & Fitch surges more than 30% after reporting surprise profit
SUMMARY: Mall apparel retailer Abercrombie & Fitch surprised investors with a fiscal first-quarter profit, sending shares surging.

TITLE: Astranis says its first internet satellite is working 'perfectly' as company prepares to bring coverage to Alaska
SUMMARY: "We have a new way of connecting people in some of the most remote and underserved parts of the world," Astranis CEO John Gedmark told CNBC.

TITLE: Mortgage demand drops again as rates cross back over 7%
SUMMARY: The average rate on the popular 30-year fixed mortgage crossed over 7% on Tuesday, according to Mortgage News Daily. The highest level since early March.

TITLE: Netflix password-sharing crackdown rolls out in the U.S.
SUMMARY: After months of anticipation, Netflix began its password-sharing crackdown in the United States.

TITLE: Nike CEO John Donahoe says brands need to stand by their values amid DeSantis, Disney feud
SUMMARY: Nike CEO John Donahoe said during the inaugural CNBC CEO Council Summit it's important for corporations to fight for the values integral to their brands.

TITLE: BlackRock bond chief Rieder says U.S. economy in 'much better shape’ than doomsayers say
SUMMARY: Rick Rieder, a three-decade market veteran who oversees $2.4 trillion for BlackRock, is optimistic about the investment outlook despite debt ceiling impasse.

TITLE: Peloton aims to rebrand as a fitness company for all with focus on app, tiered subscription pricing
SUMMARY: Peloton has long been considered an in-home bike company for fitness junkies, but the company is working to change that by making its app accessible to all.
